  "body": "This PR fixes an issue where `astream_events` failed to capture `on_chat_model_stream` events when using `create_agent`.\r\n\r\nPreviously, the `RunnableConfig` was dropped during the model execution step in `_execute_model_sync` and `_execute_model_async`, causing the underlying chat model to run without the parent callback context. This resulted in streaming responses appearing as \"all-at-once\" chunks because the token-level events were lost.\r\n\r\n**Changes:**\r\n- Updated `ModelRequest` in `langchain/agents/middleware/types.py` to accept and store an optional `config: RunnableConfig`.\r\n- Updated `model_node` and `amodel_node` in `langchain/agents/factory.py` to capture the runtime `config` and pass it to `ModelRequest`.\r\n- Updated `_execute_model_sync` and `_execute_model_async` to pass `request.config` when calling `model.invoke()` / `model.ainvoke()`.",
